  "commentary": "With SPX at 7108.11 sitting just below the GEX flip at 7113, dealers are currently in positive gamma territory and likely buying this dip given the -1.1% recent move, providing natural support around current levels. The massive negative gamma wall at 7115 (-8.2B) creates a critical inflection point where any break above would flip dealers to negative gamma, potentially accelerating moves toward the 7200 positive gamma ceiling. Key levels to watch are the 7113 flip strike for regime change and the 7115/7110 negative gamma cluster that could amplify volatility if breached, while 7200 remains the upside magnet where dealers will aggressively sell rallies.\n\nBottom line: expect buying support near current levels with potential for choppy grind higher toward 7200.",
